\begin_layout Subsection
CB Tools
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the U.S, the CB has monopoly on the cash supply.
 It can buy assets and issue short-term debt (in Israel: also 1-year debt
 is possible).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The CB can also provide loans to financial institutions, but 
\series bold
not 
\series default
directly to the government (independence of the CB).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Open market operation
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

: setting the interest rate, buying assets and foreign currencies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Today most CBs use an onvernight interest rule as the key policy tool with
 full independence.
\end_layout

